original_title: Thelonious Monk Quartet Playing at the Palais des Beaux-Arts, Brussels in 1963 - Part 1
overview: In this 1963 concert filmed at Brussel’s Palais des Beaux-Arts, Monk performs with his famous quartet consisting of himself on the piano, Charlie Rouse on tenor sax, John Ore on the double bass, and Frankie Dunlop on Drums. The quartet plays through a classic setlist of Monk’s work
title: Thelonious Monk Quartet Playing at the Palais des Beaux-Arts, Brussels in 1963 - Part 1
